text: not everyone with a #metoo is posting their story. me.too. i waited. i simply was not ready to fully elaborate if friends or family members were to ask follow-up questions. so i pretend like it didn’t happened to me. then one day when my emotions get the best of me, i broke down and told her/a significant figure in my life- out of respect i don’t want to mention her name on social media. guess what? she didn’t believe me. instead of protecting me, she choose to stand with the beast. i was hurt. i was angry at myself for letting my emotions go unchecked. perhaps if i were able to maintain my composure and deliver a more logical story line, perhaps without fountain of tears and emotional lashings, she would have believed me. for a long time, i regretted speaking up. for a long time, i were trapped between disgust, sadness and disappointment. finally i came to realized that how she react or how i feel will not change the truth. what he did were wrong and there are no excuses for that. what i needed to do is to share my story, tell young girl how to recognize such abuse and educate men/boys on how to treat women with respect. saying “metoo. i’m a victim” obviously didn’t get me very far. i promise myself i won’t shed another tear begging people to believe me. i am a survivor not a beggar. @elementshinestore #timesup #metoo #believe #survivor #iamnotavictim #educateourmen #respectwomen #protectyourself

text:
wall street rule for the #metoo era: avoid women at all cost!
.
.
no more dinners with female colleagues. don’t sit next to them on flights. book hotel rooms on different floors. avoid one-on-one meetings.

in fact, as a wealth adviser put it, just hiring a woman these days is “an unknown risk.” what if she took something he said the wrong way?

across wall street, men are adopting controversial strategies for the #metoo era and, in the process, making life even harder for women.

interviews with more than 30 senior executives suggest many are spooked by #metoo and struggling to cope. “it’s creating a sense of walking on eggshells,” said david bahnsen, a former managing director at morgan stanley who’s now an independent adviser overseeing more than $1.5 billion.

this is hardly a single-industry phenomenon, as men across the country check their behavior at work, to protect themselves in the face of what they consider unreasonable political correctness -- or to simply do the right thing. the upshot is forceful on wall street, where women are scarce in the upper ranks. the industry has also long nurtured a culture that keeps harassment complaints out of the courts and public eye, and has so far avoided a mega-scandal like the one that has engulfed harvey weinstein.
.
.
in light of the #metoo movement, and the casualties of tons of successful men who have had their lives upended by women’s accusations. the risks of working with women these days is far too high. women are setting the rules and ruining men’s’ lives over the simplest gestures, comments, even by just ignoring them. hr depts have to hire more employees to handle these females’ complaints, it’s becoming a culture and i don’t blame men for trying to protect themselves. .
.
what do you all think? 🤷‍♂️
.
.
source:
https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2018-12-03/a-wall-street-rule-for-the-metoo-era-avoid-women-at-all-cost
.
.

text:
urinary urgency and frequency
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
urinary urgency refers to the feeling of having to go to the bathroom very badly.  sometimes people get this even when their bladder is not full.  it can be very anxiety provoking!  urinary frequency refers to more than usual trips to the bathroom, both during the day and at night.

text:
at a hearing before the senate judiciary committee, christopher wylie described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters. the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like ‘drain the swamp’ or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the ‘deep state’ that weren’t necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement.

jon sharman
the independent

text: #metoo om du ännu inte sett svts dokumentär ”det slutna sällskapet” så tycker jag att du ska göra det nu. här berättar nämligen horace engdahl med flera exakt om hur unken och vidrig kvinnosyn de faktiskt har. helt öppet. utan att på något sätt be om ursäkt. för det har de aldrig behövt göra, ”så varför börja nu” verkar vara engdahls inställning. jo för att tiden kommit ikapp er, horace. den här öppenhjärtliga intervjun säger allt om hur detta kunnat pågå så länge och varför de skyddat varandra och varför de betett sig som de gjort. det har förbryllat mig länge och fram tills nu har jag letat efter svaret som jag nu till sist fått. de hatar faktiskt kvinnor. de föraktar kvinnor och ser dem på riktigt som underlägsna. sämre. han säger det rakt ut i intervjun. med ett litet skratt i ena mungipan. riv ner den här institutionen nu och skicka hem gubbjävlarna allihop. det räcker nu. och sen får det bildas en ny akademi med enbart 18 kvinnor. det kommer ta ett bra tag att balansera upp för över tvåhundra år av gubbvälde och sen om sådär tvåhundra år till så kan ni kanske släppa in 9 gubbar igen. för då möjligen har det äntligen hänt nåt. mitt förakt för horace vidriga, inhumana och förvridna inre är gränslöst. det är så jag skäms som inte förstått detta tidigare. det är ju ett monster som gömmer sig därinne bakom den prydliga slipsen och det polerade språket. en man som ingår i en akademi som alltså ska ”arbeta uppå svenska språkets renhet, styrka och höghet". språket behärskar han. men hur det är att vara människa, det har han för länge sen glömt.
name: Andreas Ibohm

text:
at a hearing before the senate judiciary committee, christopher wylie described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters. the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like ‘drain the swamp’ or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the ‘deep state’ that weren’t necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement.

jon sharman
the independent

text:
the time i wrote a song about a crush...
.
.
i try to write all types of songs and i’ve definitely wrote my share of love songs but i’ve never wrote a song about liking someone.  you see i like the feeling you get when you first start crushing on someone...especially when it’s all fresh and new.  and i think there’s more than just liking someone...you gotta like the vibe between y’all.  don’t get me wrong...love songs are dope but not everyone’s on that vibe...at least not yet.  because sometimes you can love someone and not necessarily like them and sometimes you can like someone and not necessarily love them.  but i feel like both are important and both have their time and place. .
.
so here’s my “like song”...still a work in progress...still very fresh and new...kinda like a new crush 😍💞💜 #imabeautifulmess

text:
trigger warning: mentions of sexual assault!❌ ‼️read comment‼️ almost a year ago i found myself wanting to do something that made a difference. joining learn serve international gave me the power to do so. i created it’s mine to share with the hope of helping sexual assault survivors while also giving them all the control. thus, www.itsminetoshare.org was created. 
1 in 5 women and 1 in 71 will be sexually assaulted at one point in their lives according to the nsvrc. those number should be 1 in none. i’m standing up for what i believe in the way i know how.

if you or anyone you know is a survivor of sexual assault, please check out www.itsminetoshare.org. on there, you can share your experiences anonymously or not and read other stories from survivors. as of right now, we have one, very brave individual’s, story published and i’d love to add to that.

if not to share, please check out the website and use the contact form to tell us what you think. any and all feedback is welcomed and necessary. 
before i end, i would like to say a very big thank you to @cate.c.cox for being such an important person as my partner. i can’t explain how much i appreciate and love you. and to @learnserve . you have taught me so much and without you, i wouldn’t be the woman i am today. ❤️ “even if you fail at doing something ambitious, you usually succeed in doing something important.” - peter diamandis -

text: please swipe to the video (i’ve made it blank out of respect for the people involved but listen to the words, that’s what important... it cuts off partway through but the end is about allowing yourself to cry and having your own back) these words, as well as the rest of her performance is what is allowing me to come out and share with you why i threw my underwear on stage. a lot of you have asked asked me why i did that and i hesitated to respond but this is my time to be vulnerable, to share my story and let myself move on. i have been struggling for the past year with dealing with my sexual assault. it was something that caused me to spiral back into a depression, i lost many friendships because i was no longer myself... i shut down and didn’t want to admit it. i would sit alone in my room and cry trying to remember how that happened to me that night. it’s something i never thought would happen to me, i was supposed to be strong i was supposed to be smart enough to protect myself. but it happened to me. and it has happened to so many others. the #metoo movement is not fucking new. we need to be there for each other and we need to make our voices heard and put an end to sexual violence because nobody deserves to go through this hell. so me throwing my underwear on stage was me releasing myself from the pain of that night. that was me throwing away the hurt, throwing away the fear. i’ve cried i’ve hurt but it’s time to pick myself up because i deserve better. that pair of underwear was the last painful memory of that night and now it has been replaced by a memory of the day i met the women who’s music got me through this and continues to help me fight through any obstacle that comes my way.

**repost from @seenheardbelieved ** "my forte is awkwardness" - zach galifianakis 
well, i guess it's time to introduce myself! i'm lee and i'm the 3rd featured survivor and founder/director of survivor series. i specialize in awkward moments, spreading awareness about human trafficking, educating people on the dangers of silencing/not listening to sexual violence survivors and de-frizzing my curls. i survived an assault at the age of 20 and this series is my way of preventing that from happening to another young person.  it's my dream that this community will grow and the project will reach millions of survivors and give them hope and a voice. if i can have a laugh along the way, that'd be cool too.

text:

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
#metoo
.
a woman’s work is never done
.
the midterms, the kavanaugh hearings, #metoo: what’s the state of women’s movements today? amrita basu, professor of political science and the chair of sexuality, women’s and gender studies offers her context in a conversation with writer kathy whittemore.
.
“i’m energized by teaching students here," says professor amrita basu in this wide-ranging q&a. "i find them savvy and attuned to what’s taking place in the world," she says. "compared to the time i started teaching here, they have more of a global perspective and more understanding of racial and gender inequality. they’re also able to intertwine analytical concerns with personal issues."
.
kw: i’d like to quote your own writing: “despite the strengths of women’s movements, gender inequality is systemic, severe and pervasive throughout the world. many feminist demands remain unfulfilled. many achievements have been reversed.” i’m going to ask you to go out on a limb. are we at a time to feel discouraged, or to feel hopeful? 
ab: it’s such a difficult question because i feel both. we’ve seen that the gains of feminism are not linear. we’re not going from success to greater success, in part because with achievements comes a backlash against it. 
kw: backlash seems almost organic to the process. 
ab: yes, but it also doesn’t seem that all of those gains can and will be reversed. we make progress and then we face setbacks, but that progress, those struggles, are not going to stop. right now, we’re living through such difficult times. but if you look at the numbers of women running for electoral office, the mobilizing of women, transnational connections they’re forging, the use of social media to advance feminist goals, all those things are sources of hope. 
then there is the change in the age of women who are getting involved. not long ago, younger women had this sense that feminism was passé, that women had made the gains they needed. but now, with #metoo, the women’s march on washington, what i see on college campuses is that younger women are getting involved.
.
photo by #mariastenzel. full interview at link on profile page. #amherstcollege #metoo #feminism #equality

text:
announcing duchess international magazine print copy launch!

yes! we’ve got great news and we’re super excited to share!

duchess international magazine is proud to announce the launch of her maiden print edition –‘the magnificent woman’, on sunday, 9th december 2018 at the grand ibis hotel, ikeja, lagos.

the initiative, driven by the need to improve the reading experience of our esteemed readers will provide well grounded information on lifestyle, health and wellness and fashion. 
we’ve got an interesting lineup of events: enlightening discussions, networking opportunities and high profile personalities in attendance.

outstanding individuals who have done well in their chosen fields will be honoured as well.

notable speakers and guest at the event include; dr. elishama ideh, ms. yemisi jenkins mbe, ms. bisola munis and a host of others.

let’s root for each other and watch one another grow. magnificent women we all are!

don’t be left out. save the date!

@yinka_ogundimu

announcing duchess international magazine print copy launch!

yes! we’ve got great news and we’re super excited to share!

duchess international magazine is proud to announce the launch of her maiden print edition –‘the magnificent woman’, on sunday, 9th december 2018 at the grand ibis hotel, ikeja, lagos.

the initiative, driven by the need to improve the reading experience of our esteemed readers will provide well grounded information on lifestyle, health and wellness and fashion. 
we’ve got an interesting lineup of events: enlightening discussions, networking opportunities and high profile personalities in attendance.

outstanding individuals who have done well in their chosen fields will be honoured as well.

notable speakers and guest at the event include; dr. elishama ideh, ms. yemisi jenkins mbe, ms. bisola munis and a host of others.

let’s root for each other and watch one another grow. magnificent women we all are!

don’t be left out. save the date!

@yinka_ogundimu

@huffposttaste @foxnews @nytimes bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
@huffposttaste @foxnews @nytimes bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
announcing duchess international magazine print copy launch!

yes! we’ve got great news and we’re super excited to share!

duchess international magazine is proud to announce the launch of her maiden print edition –‘the magnificent woman’, on sunday, 9th december 2018 at the grand ibis hotel, ikeja, lagos.

the initiative, driven by the need to improve the reading experience of our esteemed readers will provide well grounded information on lifestyle, health and wellness and fashion. 
we’ve got an interesting lineup of events: enlightening discussions, networking opportunities and high profile personalities in attendance.

outstanding individuals who have done well in their chosen fields will be honoured as well.

notable speakers and guest at the event include; dr. elishama ideh, ms. yemisi jenkins mbe, ms. bisola munis and a host of others.

let’s root for each other and watch one another grow. magnificent women we all are!

don’t be left out. save the date!

@yinka_ogundimu

text:
"my forte is awkwardness" - zach galifianakis 
well, i guess it's time to introduce myself! i'm lee and i'm the 3rd featured survivor and founder/director of survivor series. i specialize in awkward moments, spreading awareness about human trafficking, educating people on the dangers of silencing/not listening to sexual violence survivors and de-frizzing my curls. i survived an assault at the age of 20 and this series is my way of preventing that from happening to another young person.  it's my dream that this community will grow and the project will reach millions of survivors and give them hope and a voice. if i can have a laugh along the way, that'd be cool too.

keep following me here for my professional journey with survivor series and @leeuppity for my personal journey. 📸 by @bertaamelin
.
.
.

для вас, тупые шовинистические мужские свиньи, поясняем: хэштег #metoo, афтаром которого является данная афро–американская девушка, какбэ символизирует и означает "меня тоже сексуально домогались!" и призывает к солидарности всех жертв сексуального насилия.

тарана берк начала движение «me too» более десяти лет назад и наблюдала, как хэштег стал сплачивающим кличем после харви вайнштейна.

text: tippi hedren and alfred hitchcock for the promotion of the film "the birds" directed by alfred hitchcock, 1962 ———————————————————————— alfred hitchcock made tippi hedren a star, giving her showy roles in “the birds” and “marnie.” but when she refused the director’s sexual advances, he threatened to destroy her career. “when he told me that he would ruin me, i just told him do what he had to do,” recalls hedren. “i went out of the door and slammed it so hard that i looked back to see if it was still on its hinges.” during the shooting of their two movies, hitchcock would get jealous and resentful when he saw hedren speaking to male colleagues. at one point, when they were both in the back of a limousine, the director lunged at hedren and tried to kiss her. in another encounter, during the filming of “marnie,” hitchcock asked the actress to touch him and shared romantic fantasies with her. after she rebuffed him, he chilled toward her. “it was absolutely awful, and as soon as the movie ‘marnie’ was over, i was out of there,” she says. “that was the end of the hitchcock relationship. i finished the movie and didn’t have any other contact.” ———————————————————————— #alfredhitchcock #tocatchathief #oldhollywood #vintage #blondebombshell #classichollywood #legend #1950s #moviestar #hollywoodstar #marilynmonroe #hollywoodgreats #1960s #silverscreen #goldenage #goldenageofhollywood #elizabethtaylor #montgomeryclift #ingridbergman #tippihedren #thebirds #retro #actress #classicmovies #history #historyinpictures #marnie #metoo

text: honored to have been interviewed for @bobbyolivier “good...for a girl” article on @njdotcom (link in bio). they asked us some questions about our feelings in the #metoo era, and how it is to play music in this day and age. it was really fantastic to come together with a bunch of women, who are from all different scenes and different ages, and share battle stories.. the take away was that it really is a sea change. it definitely will get better for the future of women in music if we all stick together and rise each other up! 🙌🏻🙌🏻🙌🏻❤️❤️❤️❤️

text: as a huge advocate against domestic violence and sexual assault, dr. gratson informed us about #putthenailinit, an organization that pushes one small statement to bring about a huge difference in the world. domestic abuse statistically affects 1 out of 4 women and 1 out of 7 men, but even with this, 67% of people refuse to talk about it, let alone their experiences with the topic. this organization was formed to normalize conversation about this, creating an environment where victims can feel welcome to contribute to the dialogue instead of feeling ashamed and scared to speak up. by painting your nail of the ring finger of your left hand purple, you vow to spread awareness of the prevalence of domestic violence. this also stimulates conversation about the topic when someone asks why you have one fingernail painted. it’s important for everyone, especially on college campuses, to let sexual assault victims know that we stand with them and support them. to go through these experiences is very isolating and it’s awfully hard to speak up about, so constant support is vital. mike and i stand with you! #metoo -melissa

text:
i am debuting my first set of prints @makersmart tomorrow! the texture and color is captured beautifully and i’m over the moon about how they turned out! this piece is called women lifted and was inspired by all the women that have come before me as well as those who surround me today. i have been lifted up by so many people, including my grandma lupe who immigrated to the us as a young girl, my grandma jae who was an incredible watercolor artist, my mother who supports me through thick and thin, my mother in law, also lupe, who promptly attained us citizenship after the election of our current president, and my daughter who reminds me of what it means to be brave everyday. rosa parks, dolores huerta, anita hill, and dr. ford are just a few women who have showed me the importance of social justice and the #metoo movement. the thick layers in this piece represent the many women who have held me up and created a more just society for women to thrive. i’d love to hear about the women who have lifted you! please comment below.
.
.
lifted women is a 12”x12” giclee print with mat included for $45.00. each is numbered and signed by me. 20 total.
.
.
.
#feministart #womensrightsarehumanrights #carveouttimeforart #makersnart #painterslife #abstractacrylic #badasscreatives #sacramentoart #sacmakersmart

text:
qanon fans are applying this same participatory behavior that we have celebrated in fiction fandom to real-world political drama. and why not? the boundaries between politics and entertainment have been collapsing for years. the entire trump presidency operates like reality tv, completely divorced from any real stakes or substance.

that’s what makes this all so terrifying. do these people really believe that tom hanks and hillary clinton are personally running a massive pedophilia ring? really??? but consider this: trump announced at a rally this week that the farmers being harmed by his stupid trade war had told him “we can take it.” no actual farmers said that to him. we all know that. but it’s a little thing, just part of the story we are all interacting with.

the pulsating heart of the qanon theory is not a lunatic fringe denying the real consequences of a failing presidency. the heart of it is a devoted fan base constructing elaborate theories to make the story more fun and engaging. and if you start from the premise that nothing government does matters, then it’s easy to come along for the ride. there’s no real difference between hillary clinton and the smoke monster. they’re both just characters on the television.

that’s what alarms me most about the growth of qanon. it’s not that these people are unhinged and possibly armed. it’s that we’ve lost the capacity to treat civics, governance, and public affairs as though they have actual stakes with actual consequences. the premise of the trump presidency is that nothing matters, so you should root for your side and heckle the opposing team. he encourages his supporters to treat democrats and journalists like a rival fan base.

david karpf
medium

text:
tahirih staff across the nation sported orange today as part of un women’s #16days of activism against gender-based violence. held from november 25 – december 10, and building on the momentum of global movements such as #metoo and #timesup, this campaign brings to the forefront the voices of women and girls who have survived violence, who are defending women’s rights, and who are taking action – many of them far from the spotlight – to challenge history and affect lasting change.⠀
🔷⠀
at tahirih, we serve courageous immigrant women and girls seeking freedom from violence and the chance to live in safety and with dignity. we salute the courage, resilience, and strength of survivors, and we #orangetheworld to say no more! ⠀
🔷⠀
#teamtahirih #hearmetoo #metoo #timesup #orangetheworld #endvaw #16days #together #women #girls #immigrant #voice

text:
friendenimies

oh i remember growing up and being afraid of the dark.
terrified
spooked 😦 
i couldn’t sleep for as long as i laid in that bed in the dark.
it was for certain because every night i’d have reoccurring nightmares caused by everyday traumas .
my emotions and social skills  paid the piper.
after a while i got used to the dark 
comfortable even..
no longer afraid
my bedroom boxed me to the point i felt it served as a prison cell.
sure it gives me time to think, but i’m locked in, and i’m only going mad.
the longer i stay the more discontent is brings me ,negative memories only surround this room, makes me feel unsettled , uncomfortable in the dark..
-anonymous 🤫
*not my poem*

text:
#ஆண்மகனின் மீளா துயரம்... #நண்பர்களுக்கு சமர்பணம்... #காதல் வாழ்வு அல்ல... 👉🏻👉🏻👉🏻
இறையடி துறவேன் இன்னுயுர் பெற்றேன் அல்ல... இவ்வுயிர் விலகாமல் உன்னை விளைந்தேன்...
வெற்றிடத்தில் விட்டது பாராயோ இறைவா!!! வெற்றிடம் வெற்றி+இடம்(ஆக) மாற்றிய தருணங்களை தலை வீழும் கதை கேட்டாயோ??? இவன் கதை சரித்திரம் விதைத்தன் விளைவோ இக்கரகோசைகள்!!!
அவள் மட்டுமே வாழ்வு அல்ல நண்பா... கண் விழித்து பார்...
பாருலகில் நீ சிறு துரும்பு தானே... அச்சிறு துரும்பு கண்களில் பட்டு உறுத்தும்போது தான் இவ்வுலகம் திரும்பி பார்க்கும்...
*அனைத்தையும் காலம் மாற்றும் என்று கூறவில்லை... காலத்தை உனக்கேற்றார் போல நீ மாற்று... இவ்வுலகை உன் வசப்படுத்து... -மாற்றான் மடல்
(எண்ணங்களின் பிரதிவாதி)
#quotes #love #followforfollowback #likeforlikes #me #metoo #loveyourself #singlemom #mensfashion #tamillovefailure #lovefailurequotes #loveyourself #lovers #single #motivation #motivation

text:
chile: propuestas y debates desde el feminismo anticapitalista.
.
escribe maura galvez bernabé @mauragalvezbernabe , por juntas y a la izquierda chile @juntasyalaizquierdacl y movimiento anticapitalista
.
tomamos como punto de partida para este análisis la teoría de la reproducción social que muestra cómo la “producción de bienes y servicios y la producción de la vida son parte de un proceso integrado”, citando a tithi bhattacharya “la idea más importante de la teoría de la reproducción social es que el capitalismo es un sistema unitario que puede integrar con éxito, aunque de manera desigual, la esfera de la reproducción y la de la producción”. como bien sabemos, el capitalismo no es sólo un sistema económico que produce mercancías a costa de la explotación de trabajadores, para ello también necesita un sistema de reproducción de esa fuerza de trabajo, fuera del trabajo productivo que le permitan sostener su funcionamiento y es por ello que también es un sistema de relaciones sociales. por tanto las preguntas ¿cuáles son las causas de este momento político en particular? ¿por qué en el mundo miles de mujeres se encuentran dando luchas simultáneas? ¿cuáles con las causas de las enormes movilizaciones que se vienen dando? ¿por qué aparecen fenómenos como trump o bolsonaro? las analizamos desde ahí. a continuación esbozos de diversidad de elementos que nos parecen importantes para debatir sobre el momento actual.
.
🌐 lee el artículo completo en el link de la bio
.

text:
part two of  @somasnakeoil reflections on consent and #metoo in regards to me and what has taken place in our ・・・
consent part 4: (2 of 2) (continued.) i’m not all non judgment. sometimes i’m vicious. “what are your politics?” i attacked him, after he shared something he wrote and asked my opinion. he took a breath, then talked about unity. he compared our beliefs. i held him under a microscope. “don’t make us the same.” more than once i’ve looked him in the eyes and said, “are you a rapist?” he’s gentle with me in those moments. he listens & supports. sometimes i’m angry at him. he can be dismissive. i don’t like some of his views on life and lifestyle. and. i also see him as wise, kind, and often willing to put others needs ahead of his own. he doesn’t judge me for my sexuality or career choices or try to persuade me to change to become a good buddhist. for a period of time i became attracted to him. my experience with mentorship in the sex positive, bdsm world framed the student/teacher relationship with very different parameters. every week i went to class and took a kneeling meditation posture. the body is powerful. it felt submissive. i struggled to focus. i needed to make craving the object of meditation. i didn’t want to. aversion to desire was as extreme as desire. it brought up questions. it hurt! i finally spoke with him. i felt isolated. i didn’t want to discuss my shit with women in our sangha. in my mind, it would cause scandal. he normalized it. encouraged me to talk to other women. kept communication open, but didn’t create erotic charge. if he wanted to take advantage of power dynamic, he could have. i’m kinky as fuck and i see the world through a permissive ethical lens. he could have tried to manipulate me when i made myself vulnerable. he didn’t. it is not my place to speak to the stories of other women. my experience: i have a close student/teacher friendship with noah & he treats me with respect. one person’s experience is not everyone’s. life is not that simple. there is much for him to learn. there’s much i’m learning. we all are. and. i’m gonna keep going back to buddha school with noah, even though it’s complicated. #consent #buddhism

text:
montréal, un novembre glacial. j’ai 23 ans, je porte du rose presque chaque jour. je rentre d’une soirée à joliette, chez ma meilleure amie. je suis auprès d’elle et des trois garçons qui constituent notre famille crepuq dans un espace « safe ». je ne l’identifie pas encore ainsi, je vis simplement la symbiose. nous avons regardé des films d’horreur, sans doute mangé une poutine, fumé beaucoup de cigarettes. j’ai partagé un plaid avec le copain roux. l’autre, le théâtreux, m’appelle « ma grande ». on passe toutes nos soirées ensemble, avec nos jeunesses insolentes en médaillons et la sensation de vivre quelque chose qui comptera. qui restera.
il est minuit, peut-être passé de plusieurs heures. j’ai mon casque sur les oreilles. j’écoute encore cette variété française dont j’aurai longtemps honte, mais qui m’emporte tellement. je ne le vois pas s’asseoir. je ne vois pas non plus que le wagon se vide. je vois les titres défiler sur mon mini ipod. rose, métallisé, un cadeau de départ. 
il y a « et toute la ville en parle » dans mes oreilles quand je relève les yeux. je vois d’abord son regard, vitreux, planté dans le mien. première infraction. sa main, agitée, sur son sexe sorti. deuxième infraction. son sourire, bizarre, salivant, son sourire jeté sur moi. troisième infraction. la chanson arrive à sa fin, je suis paralysée. la peur de mourir, ou la peur juste d’entendre le son de la scène. la peur que mes jambes n’obéissent pas. 
elles n’obéiront pas. je ferai encore quatre stations, à un mètre de mon agresseur. et je ne parviendrai à me lever qu’une fois que lui sera parti, d’un pas calme, après avoir éjaculé entre nous. quatrième infraction.
hier l’histoire d’ava m’a bouleversée. je livre ici le #metoo que je n’ai pas hurlé il y a un an, pour elle et pour @bonjourlesfleurs . éduquons nos filles à se défendre, nos garçons à se conduire dignement, et envoyons des brassées d’amour aux femmes résistantes. merci @martinetjacob de m’avoir sans le savoir encouragée à l’écrire.
#desmotspourunefleur

tra i nuovi modi in cui mi propongo di usare #fb e #instagram nel nuovo anno oramai alle porte, anche questo (nuovo modo per me, intendo, immagino che molti uomini lo usino abitualmente): contattare #ragazze e #donne (che, oramai lo sappiamo, non sono anziane fino ai 75, quindi vedete un po' voi), contattare, dicevo, donne più o meno giovani per chiedere loro, candidamente, come so essere candido io, foto della loro, diciamo così, intimità più segreta. si accettano anche volontarie. (anzi, qualcuna di voi ha già fatto la sua parte con invidiabile sollecitudine, pur non essendo stata in alcun modo da me sollecitata. cosa di cui ringrazio)

text: i love an intentional meeting of the minds 🖤 went to a panel last night revolving around the #metoo movement and how it’s impacted our community on a local level. a huge takeaway was the continual marginalization of trans women of color, and the unfortunate power of silence. did you know jacksonville has the nation’s highest rate of murder for trans women of color? i didn’t before last night. shout out to anyone living their truth in this city, you are a fucking powerhouse just for having the courage to be.

“this is bigger than a moment. we are in a movement.” — @taranaburke on #metoo #16days #repost @ted ・・・
in 2006, civil rights activist tarana burke sat in her room, took out a piece of paper, wrote “me too” across the top, and created an action plan for a movement that supported all survivors of sexual violence. now, #metoo has become a global movement, and while its mission is often misinterpreted, tarana is determined to keep working to dismantle the building blocks of sexual violence: power and privilege. “power and privilege doesn't always have to destroy and take -- it can be used to serve and build,” she says. to watch her ted talk from #tedwomen, visit go.ted.com/taranaburke

text: i have debated on writing this post when the day comes and the day is now and i am still unsure how to verbalize my feelings into thoughts. i struggle between vulnerably and secrecy but i feel i should be honest while writing this and be straight forward. i lost my virginity via rape 7 years ago today. i had just turned 17 years old. it would hurt me in waves throughout the next years of my life. it affected me in different ways. sometimes in an overwhelming rush i would break into panic attacks and other times i could easily erase it from my mind like it never happened. fast forward to mid 2018 and i started having severe ptsd out of nowhere. remembering things i hadn’t remembered in years, things i had blacked out, small details i had forgotten. i thought it would never end. i am explaining this part to explain the increasing severity of the situation. anyways, i started receiving psychiatric care and eventually underwent emdr therapy. (eye movement desensitization and reprocessing) it’s a type of therapy that involves reprocessing traumatic memories in the brain using bilateral stimulation and eye movements to reprogram the memory to be non-traumatic for the individual. 3 sessions and it changed my life. i want you anyone to know that’s gone through something like this, that you’re not alone and it can get better. you will heal and move on. this is the proof. i had planned this summer that on this day i would out my rapist on social media platforms, drop names and everything. i was sick of no one knowing and him getting to continued to live his life without consequences. after therapy this summer, i no longer have a desire to write names or explain the hurt. i now want to explain the future healing you can provide for yourself. love yourself, get help, talk about it. you’re stronger than you will ever realize. i love people and i will not let one individual make me cynical or hateful of humanity and you shouldn’t either. but this picture is me now. after all the hurt and the sadness, i’m here. i’m stronger, happier, and i’m learning to love myself more and more everyday💕 #metoo #emdrtherapy #edmr #selflove

text:
in a 1,400-word letter published in @hollywoodreporter, @lenadunham atoned for publicly doubting actress @auroraperrineau when she came forward last november with claims of sexual assault — rape when she was 17 years old — against murray miller, an executive producer on “girls.” dunham, to the shock of many feminists, took his side saying, “while our first instinct is to listen to every woman’s story, our insider knowledge of murray’s situation makes us confident that sadly this accusation is one of the 3 percent of assault cases that are misreported every year,” said the statement along with co-showrunner @jennikonner.
•
on wednesday, dunham described that initial response as “inexcusable” and “a terrible mistake,” and issued a lengthy public apology to perrineau. the internet wasn’t having it. many questioned why she would issue a long and drawn-out public apology, more than a year after the fact. closing out her letter, dunham explained that she hoped her admission would lead to “healing"" and acknowledged that she wasn’t likely to win over any new fans. “there are some who will think i am writing this to curry public favor,” she wrote, adding in a parenthetical: “that’s ok, though, i stopped thinking that was an option for me somewhere around 2014, and that’s some kind of freedom.” (photo by jordan strauss / invision / ap; illustration by @thelilynews)
name: The Lily

text:
ernesto gazzeri
roma,  1866 - 1965 /eng/  apollo and daphne

i hope that some day women would go outside without feeling insecure.
or show our bodies without being sexualized.
without being criticized for the clothes were're wearing.
have the same rights and oportunities as men.
don't be judge for how many people we sleep with.
and that people believe us when we say that we've been ripped or had suffer sexual abuse. 
it's hard, but we can fight against this patriarchal world.

i've never lived something so hard, but i dont know if some day will happend to me or any friend,
and that's scary and terrifying, don't you think so? 
this thoughts are always in my mind and i wantéd to share with you . that's all, i hope you have a nice weekend.

#metoo
#nomeansno /esp/  apolo y dafne

espero que algún dia las mujeres podamos salir sin sentirnos inseguras.
o enseñar nuestros cuerpos sin ser sexualizados.
sin ser criticadas por la ropa que llevemos.
tener los mismos derechos y oportunidades que los hombres.
no ser juzgadas por cuantas personas nos acostemos.
y que la gente nos crea cuando decimos que hemos sido violadas o hemos sufrido abuso sexual.
es duro que podemos luchar contra ente mundo patriarcal.

nunca he vivido algo tan fuerte, pero no sé si algún dia me ocurrirá a mí o a alguna amiga, y da miedo ¿no creeis?

estos pensamientos están siempre en mi mente y quería compartirla con vosotros. eso es todo, espero que tengais
un bonito fin de semana.

#metoo
#noesno  mt

i have never lived something so hard, but i do not know if some day will happend to me or any friend,
and that's scary and terrifying, do not you think so? 
this thoughts are always in my mind and i wantéd to share with you . that's all, i hope you have a nice weekend.

etoo
 /esp/  apolo y dafne

espero que algún dia las mujeres podamos salir sin sentirnos inseguras.
o enseñar nuestros cuerpos sin ser sexualizados.
sin ser criticadas por la ropa que llevemos.
tener los mismos derechos y opounidades que los hombres.
no ser juzgadas por cuantas personas nos acostemos.
y que la gente nos crea cuando decimos que hemos sido violadas o hemos sufrido abuso sexual.
es duro que podemos luchar contra ente mundo patriarcal.

nunca he vivido algo tan fuee, pero no sé si algún dia me ocurrirá a mí o a alguna amiga, y da miedo ¿no creeis?

estos pensamientos están siempre en mi mente y quería compairla con vosotros. eso es todo, espero que tengais
un bonito fin de semana.

etoo

text:
a new survey of attitudes to rape and sexual violence published today (6 december) by the end violence against women coalition reveals:
-
a third (33%) of people in britain think it isn’t usually rape if a woman is pressured into having sex but there is no physical violence #nomeansno
-
a third of men think if a woman has flirted on a date it generally wouldn’t count as rape, even if she hasn’t explicitly consented to sex (compared with 21% of women) #thisisnotconsent
-
a third of men also believe a woman can’t change her mind after sex has started #nomeansno
-
almost a quarter (24%) think that sex without consent in long-term relationships is usually not rape #thisisnotconsent
-
these figures are so alarming! that's a huge proportion of adults in britain (people who make up juries on rape trials) that are very unclear about what rape is.
-
if you've been affected by this issue please reach out to manchester rape crisis. ❤️.
.
.
.

text:
rise was able to provide these crucial services in 2017 because of donations from you - our rise community.
.
the #metoo movement has changed the way sexual abuse, sexual assault, and intimate partner violence are talked about. many more people feel comfortable reporting their abuse and seeking help than ever before! this wonderful movement has created a much greater need for rise services than ever before and our services have been overwhelmed in 2018.
.
so we are asking for your help. we are hoping to reach our fundraising goal of $40,000 by the end of the year. this money will fund our services for 2019 and allow more survivors to have access to the help they deserve.
.
please consider donating to rise - any amount is incredibly generous and helpful. talk to family and friends, motivate others to get involved!
.
thank you for being part of our wonderful community.
.
donate at www.riseslo.org

text: after moving to the big city i tried to fit in the corporate world. it was like trying to put a square peg in a round hole. i hated it. now that i am back to being a server at a restaurant i found my joy again - i am the oldest one who works there but i fit right in. during my shifts i like to remind god of my age and ask for the energy to keep up. trusting he will sustain me until i’m ready for what’s next. last night one of my bosses told me i was a treasure.  knowing god used that young man to tell me that - affirming i am where i’m suppose to  be - being me. #hope hope #faith #joy #love #myblinddatewithgod #acquitted #jesus #shine #thrive #conqueror #victory #server #corporate #metoo #overcome #beyou #now

text:
experimenting with loving all the little intricacies of my body. beautiful pieces often overlooked in favour of focusing on the parts society convinces us to constantly fret over or hate. i think it's essential for all, but especially for women to stop and take moments to reclaim our bodies as our own. one piece at a time, and really marvel at all that our physical and mental bodies endure, and even more what they are capable of, what power each piece holds. how powerful would we feel if we were taught to value our beautiful bodies and minds as our own? .
.

shared parental leave, flexible working, part-time working and job share opportunities remain either a novelty or limited rather than valuable tools for advancing careers. and i can’t help but wonder, if shared parental leave became more commonplace, would male colleagues be viewed with paternal suspicion.

created by the united nations general assembly in july 2010, un women works to protect the rights of women and girls, to further their health and economic empowerment, as well as to increase women’s and girls’ involvement in politics, civil society, and public life. the organisation works with governments and civil society organisations to formulate policies, laws and programmes so that global standards to achieve gender equality are met.

while progress has been made on several fronts, inequalities for females remain deeply entrenched in the society and starkly visible across the world. in times when movements like #metoo have gained popularity, women from marginalised backgrounds struggle for recognition.

being cognizant of the fact that the opportunity of a generation rests in our collective understanding of gender inequality, confero model united nations 2019 presents the third committee, un women, to be held on 30th-31st march 2019, at s.g.t.b. khalsa college, university of delhi.

text:
we are one year in!!! everyday i am putting one foot in front of the other trusting god with this vision. as a leader i’m learning all of the ways to succeed and fail at the same time. this year i have been driving myself up a wall about what i did, what i didn’t do, & and how i’m going to do. but i’m learning that my failures don’t count me out they just build me up. and everything that does not work out is not a failure. i am so grateful for everyone that has played a role in building this platform whether you attended a bootcamp or donated monetarily or with your time and service. special so to my team @donicarenee @eleven_twenty_3 @brownsugarkoko @honey_badger_d.g.a.f @ms.phdeed @mom_of_reaganelise @donvsdiva @inmyskinnn ———————————————-
one of the most impactful gems i’ve caught this year is that in time god makes everything beautiful. i’m learning to be patient with myself and this journey. taking my hands off the wheel and letting god remain in control. understanding that his promise does not return void. 
#fbf #iabbgotabirthday #metoo #childsexualabuseawareness #mentalhealthawareness #iambeautifulbecause #womenempowerment #womenempoweringgirls

text:
76/100 ::gutted of trust:: rape is not one moment, one situation, it is falling into a void that undoes all safety in all directions, it is a poison that fractures life forward, tears up everything, it lays wire for decades of explosives—projections that lay you right back in the line of fire of the moment of trauma. it can only be us, awake and witnessing ourself and our pain, with a will to heal our heart, who can with our own hands finally drive the darkness back.
.
i still fall to darkness. child abuse and rape tore self-trust out of my being, a wound that is still laid bare—especially when stepping into the unknown of transition, when jumping off cliffs of yesterday to discover my future, when i am called to trust myself and let go so i can arrive—it’s here where all the pain of being told that i chose to be hurt, the deep regret i felt for believing i made myself suffer, for not being able to protect myself—tries to make me falter, it covers me like a heavy wave, a physical pain, it crushes me. like a fever i can only wait for it to pass, to witness with compassion the deep depths of suffering that still ring through my body. forging a new life calls for a confidence i am newly learning, rallying against those old patterns of fear hurts, a contraction before birth, it’s amazingly painful.
.
there is a part of me still so utterly terrified. she is a little girl—gutted, bloody, like a wild animal careening through violence and clinging to her life—she is pure survival and she trusts no one. no one.
.
she will never trust anyone until she trusts me. when it is hardest, when the pain is so great, when fear and doubt swallow me whole, this is when it’s most important i reach inside and lift her wild mangled body, hold her close. “i am an adult with resources and strength. i know in my heart what is best for me and my family. i deserve a beautiful life and i know how to build it, i am safe and free in the unknown. the violence is over because i saved myself.” when that little girl is able to feel trust in her body she will finally be able to soften from her former position in war, and breathe deeply the freedom she already has but can’t yet feel.

text:
do. not. silence. your. opposition.

we have such brittle, grievance-jockeying, competitive-victimhood sensationalism on all sides of the political spectrum because we've romanticized tribalism and over-policed ideas/language. every camp feels hard done by. #blacklivesmatter started out of necessity, then fragile white people had to remind us that "white people have issues too!" #metoo  began to air out how frequent/common rape is, people who simply don't get along used it as a platform to lambaste each other over completely unrelated shit.

we've fetishized punishment/exiling those who we deem opposition is because our critical thinking skills have become weak. social media allows us to curate our exposure to whatever supports our view and we call anyone a genius/revolutionary just so long as they articulate what we already believe. we no longer know how to handle opposition or adversity.

you should want to hear the best arguments for the shit you disagree with. i want to hear the entire world's absolute best argument for every single prejudice. i want to hear the most articulated and reasonable justifications the world has to offer for racism, sexism, classism, ableism, transphobia, xenophobia ans ageism. because i want to be bolstered enough in why i believe in the opposite of these things enough that i can rationally dissect and destroy each argument for them. expose the root issues of your opposition, not by silencing or blacklisting them, but by criticising their ideas. instead, we write hitpieces, the left denounces the not-like-them-enough as "alt-right" and the right denounces the not-like-them-enough as "liberal cucks". the path to progress isn't paved on the road of pulling the plug on the speaker of those you disagree with, but rather by articulating why your idea is the better idea.

were you born woke? have you never been wrong about anything in your entire life? do you still believe everything you believed fifteen years ago? engage with the best arguments. you'll learn more and maybe grow yourself.

you don't know you're on a leash if you sit next to the peg all day.

photo by @danimuze from our shoot with @sangdulait

we have such brittle, grievance-jockeying, competitive-victimhood sensationalism on all sides of the political spectrum because we've romanticized tribalism and over-policed ideas/language. every camp feels hard done by. #blacklivesmatter started out of necessity, then fragile white people had to remind us that "white people have issues too!" #metoo  began to air out how frequent/common rape is, people who simply do not get along used it as a platform to lambaste each other over completely unrelated shit.

we've fetishized punishment/exiling those who we deem opposition is because our critical thinking skills have become weak. social media allows us to curate our exposure to whatever supports our view and we call anyone a genius/revolutionary just so long as they articulate what we already believe. we no longer know how to handle opposition or adversity.

you should want to hear the best arguments for the shit you disagree with. i want to hear the entire world's absolute best argument for every single prejudice. i want to hear the most articulated and reasonable justifications the world has to offer for racism, sexism, classism, ableism, transphobia, xenophobia ans ageism. because i want to be bolstered enough in why i believe in the opposite of these things enough that i can rationally dissect and destroy each argument for them. expose the root issues of your opposition, not by silencing or blacklisting them, but by criticising their ideas. instead, we write hitpieces, the left denounces the not-like-them-enough as "alt-right" and the right denounces the not-like-them-enough as "liberal cucks". the path to progress is not paved on the road of pulling the plug on the speaker of those you disagree with, but rather by articulating why your idea is the better idea.

were you born woke? have you never been wrong about anything in your entire life? do you still believe everything you believed fifteen years ago? engage with the best arguments. you'll learn more and maybe grow yourself.

you do not know you are on a leash if you sit next to the peg all day.

text:
heb jij een controleverslaving? 
óf weet jij wanneer de gezonde grens bereikt is..? hoi, ik ben farah. controleverslaafd. 😅 sinds dat ik dit besef, werk ik toe naar een checklist-loos leven. 🤗 
we zijn sneller verslaafd als dat je denkt! want hoeveel checklijstjes heb jij? en hoe reageer je als het niet loopt zoals 'gepland'..? ik ben erachter gekomen dat het doel dat ik hiermee nastreef een grote illusie blijkt te zijn. 
maar controle hebben is wel gewoon fijn. maar waarom dan? 
het controlegedrag is namelijk iets wat we als mens van nature al inzetten bij het creëren van een veilige omgeving en zekerheid voor zowel jezelf als voor anderen. 
toch wisten velen onder ons - #metoo 😉 - hier een grens te overschrijden.

ik heb hierover een artikel geschreven waarin ik het inzicht deel wat mij heeft wakker geschud. sindsdien ervaar ik échte rust! ik vertel je ook over de meest voorkomende signalen van een obsessieve controleur. dus aan de slag en controleer jezelf maar!😌 link artikel: www.connect2unite.nl/controleverslaving

text: jeg fikk gleden av å åpne siste dag av ylfs høstkonferanse. jeg snakket om #metoo og maktmisbruk ved norske sykehus. det er første gang jeg har fortalt hele min historie ufiltrert - det var faktisk mer stress enn jeg trodde. men for en fantastisk kjærlighet fra publikum❤️ da jeg var ferdig med doktorgraden i vinter, og ikke lenger bundet til avdelingen, gikk jeg mange runder med meg selv om jeg skulle si fra eller ikke. #utentaushetplikt hadde fått stor oppslutning blant leger - nesten 4000 signerte og mange sjokkerende historier kom frem. jet har selv opplevd ting som er uttafor, og sett og hørt ting som er enda mer uttafor.  men det hadde ikke vært noen reaksjon fra sykehusene. det er den letteste og vanskeligste avgjørelsen jeg har tatt. lett fordi noen må si fra. vanskelig fordi jeg skjønte at det sannsynligvis betød at jeg kom til å måtte slutte. men nettopp når man har noe å tape er det viktig å si fra. for å ubeskjedent sitere en klok mann «jeg har ønsket å være en stemme for de som ikke selv fant ord.» tusen takk for meg @yngreleger, og takk for bunnsolid støtte hele veien!😍

text:
portrait of marta montero, mother of lucia perez. "el año que viene lù, nos vamos a ir juntas en buenos aires asi la conocemos".
"bueno mamà" me dice. "desgraciadamente nunca pudo traerla y cuando venia por acá el pasado lunes con la tia me acordé de eso y pensé: bueno lucia, buenos aires la vas a conocer. aun que sea te voy a llevar en mi corazón y con tu foto. y hoy veo todas estas fotos que han traído ustedes, todas estas fotos arriba y lucia la está conociendo desde el cielo buenos aires. 
no es casualidad lo que hicieron con lucia. 
miren cuantas lucias me estan mirando! ustedes son lucía. cada una de ustedes son la voz de lucía, de esa chica que no empezó a vivir cuando le cortaron las alas y la mataron". a lucía pérez la mataron dos veces, una sus asesinos y otra la justicia patriarcal.
#justiciaporlucia
ph © karl mancini
#reportage #photojournalism #argentina #buenosaires #portrait #mother #women #womenrights #niunamenos #picoftheday #followme #gender #genderbasedviolence #metoo #documentary #project

text:
to ban or not to ban? why are people searching for evil today? this topic of conversation has come up with many people over the past few days. i love this article and the last three paragraphs make perfect sense to me. not just for just this topic but all controversial topics today. believe me i get the whole #metoo movement but seriously? it’s a song from decades ago when men practiced chivalry and this song is nothing but an innocent and sweet song and i find it quite romantic. because that is what the intent of the song was back then. i will continue to sing it and play it for as long as i live. if i have a child i will teach them what is right and wrong and not leave it up to a song to do that. 💥💥#justlyrics #romance #chivalry #dontruinagoodthing #lookforthegood #babyitscoldoutside “women deserve better than lazy, intentionally uncharitable readings of half-a-century-old songs for their feminist causes. people, romance and sexuality are complex, so taking a catchy tune and highlighting the portions that sound most suspicious in 2018 is not just a stretch — it's dishonest.

unilaterally moralizing that songs, movies, novels, or any art from another time is no longer fit for public consumption sends us down a no-win path. it leaves so many valued cultural artifacts vulnerable to puritanical erasure – whether it happens overnight or over time – and robs us of opportunities to continue seeing ourselves in other humans, stories and cultures from our past. 
going out of our way to find evil interpretations of classic art doesn't further a feminist agenda, but engaging with and analyzing older works such as baby, it's cold outside just might. but that can only happen if people actually hear the song.” 💥read the full article here https://www.cbc.ca/news/opinion/baby-its-cold-outside-1.4936071
name: Nadia Zaraweh

unilaterally moralizing that songs, movies, novels, or any a from another time is no longer fit for public consumption sends us down a no-win path. it leaves so many valued cultural aifacts vulnerable to puritanical erasure – whether it happens overnight or over time – and robs us of oppounities to continue seeing ourselves in other humans, stories and cultures from our past. 
going out of our way to find evil interpretations of classic a does not fuher a feminist agenda, but engaging with and analyzing older works such as baby, it is cold outside just might. but that can only happen if people actually hear the song.” 💥read the full aicle here

text:
hej @svt . i inledning av ert sändningstillstånd finner jag formuleringen; ”verksamheten ska präglas av oberoende och stark integritet och bedrivas självständigt i förhållande till såväl staten som olika ekonomiska, politiska och andra intressen och maktsfärer i samhället.” ni har i alla tider varit en normerande kraft. ni har gett oss perspektiven vi många gånger saknat. delat stora som små berättelser från världens alla hörn. avslöjat orättvisor och missförhållanden lokalt likväl som globalt. ni har gett annorlunda människor plats, främjat olikheter, gjort oss mer toleranta och accepterande mer nyfikna och öppna. ni har lyft minoriteters kamp och allas lika rättigheter. ni har lärt oss räkna, läsa och förstå. för det är jag tacksam men precis som fredrik backman skriver i björnstad så är ju kultur både ”allt vi uppmuntrar och allt vi tillåter” och här börjar det skava för mig. 
under och efter vittnesmålen i #metoo börjar jag mer och mer förstå att ni samtidigt som ni gett oss allt vi har att vara tacksamma för också varit mer eller mindre avgörande för den sortens kultur som möjliggjort att normerande män med makt i decennier kunnat begå övergrepp och sexuellt våld mot kvinnor. ni har både indirekt och direkt gett män makt och möjlighet att bete sig illa för det har aldrig funnits några vägledande konsekvenser. ni har snarare tvärtom varit oerhört toleranta, förlängt kontrakt, höjt löner, tilldelat huvudroller och programledaruppdrag år ut och år in. trots att ni många gånger vetat om deras gränsöverskridande beteenden både i jobbet och privat. ni har under årtionden varit helt avgörande för att skitbeteenden och övergrepp har kunnat pågått. så här ett år efter #metoo så blir jag därför förvånad när ni väljer en man att ringa in nyåret som för så många av oss förkroppsligar #metoo och den kultur som vi nu vill lämna bakom oss. jag undrar om ni anser att ni hedrar ert uppdrag med det valet. jag undrar om ni anser att det här är ert sätt att visa att ni tar vittnesmålen under #metoo på allvar? integritet? jag undrar en massa mer saker men kanske att ni kan förklara det närmast obegripliga till att börja med? tacksam för svar/ p #ringvarningsklockaring

under och efter vittnesmålen i  börjar jag mer och mer förstå att ni samtidigt som ni gett oss allt vi har att vara tacksamma för också varit mer eller mindre avgörande för den soens kultur som möjliggjo att normerande män med makt i decennier kunnat begå övergrepp och sexuellt våld mot kvinnor. ni har både indirekt och direkt gett män makt och möjlighet att bete sig illa för det har aldrig funnits några vägledande konsekvenser. ni har snarare tväom varit oerhö toleranta, förlängt kontrakt, höjt löner, tilldelat huvudroller och programledaruppdrag år ut och år in. trots att ni många gånger vetat om deras gränsöverskridande beteenden både i jobbet och privat. ni har under åionden varit helt avgörande för att skitbeteenden och övergrepp har kunnat pågått. så här ett år efter  så blir jag därför förvånad när ni väljer en man att ringa in nyåret som för så många av oss förkroppsligar  och den kultur som vi nu vill lämna bakom oss. jag undrar om ni anser att ni hedrar e uppdrag med det valet. jag undrar om ni anser att det här är e sätt att visa att ni tar vittnesmålen under  på allvar? integritet? jag undrar en massa mer saker men kanske att ni kan förklara det närmast obegripliga till att börja med? tacksam för svar/ p

text:
today we released awakened voice's new blog, the nightingale! as an extension of the awakened voices literary magazine, we seek to provide a platform for even more writers to share their voices. writing allows one’s voice to contribute to a larger narrative, and most of all to be heard, understood, and supported by a community.
.
.
at the nightingale, we’re excited to host your writing – we want to share more voices so that more people can listen to them. we want to be part of an honest, healing conversation about sexual violence, and we want you here with us. if you like, you can leave a comment below to share some of your thoughts on how writing has helped you heal, or if you’re interested in having your writing published on the nightingale, you can take a look at our submission guidelines on our website.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#chicagoart #chicagononprofit #chicagogallery #advocacy#survivorart #artsed#artwatchers #metoo#believesurvivors #metoomvmt #affirmations #creativewriting #poems

text: and how was your week? 🤗 mine was mind blowing fantastic! ❤️ when we follow the path that’s meant to be things can suddenly go at lightning speed. and that’s exactly what’s been happening to me lately. good thing i chose a very sporty vehicle (physical body) for this life here on earth to keep up 🔥😉 this week i’ve been on ‘charity hunt’, made a beautiful commitment, practiced my english writing, made the final selection of poems that will be printed, and we’re making awesome progress with the corporate identity! 🌟 i will most certainly tell you all about it later on but first i’m gonna celebrate life like i never did before 💫💃🥂🕺💫 wishing you the same, have a mind blowing fantastic weekend everyone! 🎉😍

i’m so grateful to have this project up and running to help those who would like to give #arttherapy a try or who have found it to be very helpful. for me, i believe it saved my life. it gives me purpose and tranquility. they say time can heal all wounds, well that wasn’t working for me. i was angry and confused and i felt like i had nothing to offer, because it was robbed from me. when i discovered ceramics in college it all started to change. i was good at it and that made me feel so amazing! it was so healing and i didn’t realize my growth while it happened. hours spent working with my hands and brain and being completely at peace. surrounded by woman and men who loved and supported the craft. artists are such happy and kind people. i realized that all the shit i was holding onto was my real demon. i only had myself to be mad at because i wouldn’t allow myself to grow and move on. and i swear sitting at the spinning wheel and having my hands move and transform the clay into vessels was what caused my own release from all my pain and anger and confusion. all the sudden i transformed just like the clay and man was it powerful. later on in college i was asked to make a raku project (hand built) i made little faceless lady figurines with exaggerated curves to represent how i felt people saw me, for a body and never a soul. i then smashed the ladies after they were rakued and i repaired them with gold, a japanese style of fixing pottery called kintsugi. it showed me that i was stronger and more beautiful, that all the challenges made me even better. made me who i am today and i’m very proud of the woman i have become! i was finally able to express myself and my feelings and process them through the art of creating! 💕 i hope more people experience that kind of healing! thank you so much if you made it this far, i know this was a long one!

text:
shockingly, one in 10 people asked weren’t sure or didn’t think it was rape to have sex with a woman who was very drunk or asleep. (evaw coalition report, 2018) 
as we enter the festive season when many will be attending parties or perhaps drinking more than usual, it’s crucial we make this very, very clear. 
sex with someone who is incapacitated or unable to make informed consent is rape. drinking doesn’t mean she’s asking for it; it’s not a green light to take advantage. there is no excuse. rape, is rape.

text:
@thejimmydoreshow @bbcnews @nbcnews @anakasparianofficial @turunsanomat - bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
mónica ramírez and mily treviño-sauceda — @campesinasunite 
mily treviño-sauceda and mónica ramírez are co-founders of the alianza nacional de campesinas, the first national organization serving the interests of the country’s 700,000 farmworker women in their fight against workplace exploitation and sexual harassment. treviño-sauceda, who worked in the agriculture fields of coachella valley, california, alongside her family from the age of 8 until 23, is considered the founder of the farmworker women’s movement in the united states. ramírez, the daughter and granddaughter of farmworkers, has dedicated her career to advocating for latina and immigrant women and promoting women’s leadership. #smithsonian #smithsonianingenuity 
#metoo 📸 @aspictures

text:
i don’t see enough white women talking about the latest @lenadunham dumpster fire. .
.
lena silenced a black woman who was brave enough to come out against a rapist, which she passed a polygraph for: fucking insane btw: what women have to go through to prove they were assaulted. (and then the charges against murray miller were dropped anyway). please believe women. i’m still healing from my worst assault by a man of power but in addition, i’m healing from the backlash i received for doing so. sometimes that hurts worse. but no one came out against me unsolicited + centered themselves in a public statement like lena did. .
.
aurora perrineau was 17 yrs old when she woke up under an older white man of power having sex with her. it took her years but the fire of the #metoo movement (launched by @taranajaneen ) gave her the courage. .
.
after years of building that courage as a woc in a white man’s world (hollywood) she told her story. in a self centering “apology” lena admits she used her power to publicly accuse aurora of lying, when *lena* was actually lying. .
.
she not only silenced another woman but a woc. this is a painful violent pattern: the voices of woc have been endlessly violently marginalized + silenced by white women.
.
she threw a woc under the bus to protect a lying white man. .
this is not a minor slip. this is a major moment to understand why white feminism is so violent + ww are not trusted. pay attention. follow bipoc, stay silent + respectful in their spaces, google what you don’t understand, pay a bipoc to help you unpack your privilege, disrupt the dinner table. there is no dismantling patriarchy without dismantling racism. follow @gutsygirlart @rachel.cargle @laylafsaad @shishi.rose @kimcrayton1 @leesareneehall @adriennemareebrown @ihartericka @mckensiemack @sassy_latte @iamrachelricketts + let them lead you to more woc. do the work. if i, if you, say something wrong, + i will + we will, allow yourself to be taught. there is a lifetime of unlearning to do. the fact that lena limited the comments on her problematic last post proves an unwillingness to learn. don’t be fragile, be strong, be willing to be wrong.

une chanson pour faire connaître #lepointnoir by @iamnoormusic #blackdot #blackdotfrance #metoo #timesup #itsonus . fr | à l’origine, la « black dot campaign » a été créée en 2015 en grande-bretagne, de façon informelle sur facebook par une ex-victime de violences conjugales qui a souhaité conserver l’anonymat.
✋⚫ le principe est simple : avec un point noir dessiné sur la paume de la main (avec un crayon à maquillage par exemple), puis en montrant ce signal à une personne de confiance, on lance un appel à l’aide pour violence.s et on exprime une difficulté à en parler librement.
la personne qui reçoit le message a pour mission d'engager une conversation discrètement, et d'aider la victime à s'orienter vers des professionnels.
#lepointnoir

en | originally, the black dot campaign was created in 2015 in britain, informally on facebook by an ex-victim of domestic violence who wished to remain anonymous.
✋⚫ the principle is simple : with a black dot drawn in the palm of the hand (with a make-up pencil, for example), then
showing this signal to a trusted person, is launching a call for help for violence.s, and tells a difficulty to talk about it.
the person who receives the message has the mission to discretely engage a conversation and help the victim to get in touch with competent services.
#blackdotfrance #blackdot

text:
@pizzahut @mcdonalds @tommyhilfiger @huffposttaste @foxnews @nytimes bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

_
so to anyone out there who wants to be the next @brianmayforreal (astrophysicists, singer, song writer, musician to queen and more) or hedy lamarr (actress/scientist) i say go for it! you shouldn’t  have to chose one or the other, some people can only do one thing at a time and others make it work!

text:
@pizzahut @mcdonalds @tommyhilfiger @huffposttaste @foxnews @nytimes bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

cnn

text: quem nasceu a partir de fevereiro dos anos de 1936, 1948, 1960, 1972, 1984, 1996, 2008 ou faz aniversário no período de 7 de dezembro a 5 de janeiro, tem o signo de rato no mapa chinês. 🎯 imagine aqui o ratinho de laboratório, aquele que se perde no labirinto dos pensamentos, pensa e repensa situações. 🎯 e também aquele que usa de coerência e lógica para encontrar a saída e resolver tudo o que precisa ser feito. 🐀 inteligente, curioso, rápido, controlado, presta atenção em tudo, aprende com muita rapidez e possui uma excelente capacidade de execução. 🚫 no desequilíbrio deste signo aparece dificuldade em se entregar, medo, desconfiança, mágoa, ressentimento, crítica e auto crítica, menos valia, falta de autoconfiança e mesquinhez. 👣💗 #psicomatriz

text:
“the main point of my story is the changes that occur within a person... our parents raise us in a certain way, but we have the power to change and be different. in chile, we have situations of domestic violence and situations where women are killed. kids grow up watching and learning about that. like in my case. we can be more passive or active about that.” p:chile:2018
•••••
for the 16 days of activism, footage will focus on “women ending conflict” by launching a campaign from our girl-talk-girl program featuring new stories from and produced by young women in the school of psychology at pontificia universidad católica de chile. each young woman is the first person in her family to attend university. gtg provides a safe platform for global young women to share experiences of gender-based violence and to heal. [girl-talk-girl was generously funded by the us embassy in santiago and by donors like you.].
.
.
.

.
1. feel gratitude now for what you currently have. feel your body and appreciate all the beautiful ways it supports you. see the abundance that surrounds you now--love, money, time. there is a vibration to everything you have now and it's only with you because you put your attention on it a few years ago. that's why it's here! tap into that vibration daily and be grateful🙏. journal, visualize, meditate...feel it.
